items.title: Minneapolis: 37-year old Alex Pretti killed by ICE agents
items.standfirst: For the second time this month, a U.S. citizen was shot and killed by a federal agent in Minneapolis when 37-year-old Alex Pretti was killed during a federal immigration operation — sparking a candlelight vigil and renewed shock in the city still reeling from the death of Renee Good less than three weeks earlier — and in both cases state and federal officials have offered conflicting accounts of what happened, with Minnesota’s governor vehemently rejecting the federal narrative. France24 correspondent Jessica Le Masurier reports from Minneapolis.

items.title: Tehran warn it will treat any US strike as an "all-out-war"
items.standfirst: Iran will treat any attack "as an all-out war against us," a senior Iranian official said on Friday, ahead of the arrival of a U.S. military aircraft carrier strike group and other assets in the Middle East in the coming days. "This military buildup - we hope it is not intended for real confrontation - but our military is ready for the worst-case scenario. This is why everything is on high alert in Iran," said the senior Iranian official, speaking on condition of anonymity. Shirli Sitbon reports.
